    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix eNB_send_MBMS_SESSION_START_FAILURE missing required IEs\n\n### Summary\nThe function `eNB_send_MBMS_SESSION_START_FAILURE` was not properly encoding all required Information Elements in the M2AP SessionStartFailure message. This caused issues when the function was called during MBMS session establishment failures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_eNB_interface_management.c`: Added missing ENB_MBMS_M2AP_ID IE to SessionStartFailure message\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_eNB_interface_management.c`: Fixed incorrect error log message\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_eNB_interface_management.c`: Improved function structure to match successful response pattern\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `eNB_send_MBMS_SESSION_START_FAILURE()` during MBMS session setup, the M2AP message encoding would fail or produce incomplete messages due to missing required IEs. This resulted in:\n- Incomplete M2AP SessionStartFailure messages being sent\n- Incorrect error logging showing \"Failed to encode M2 setup request\" instead of proper failure message\n- Potential interoperability issues with MCE nodes expecting complete message structures\n\nThe fix ensures that both MCE_MBMS_M2AP_ID and ENB_MBMS_M2AP_ID are properly included in the failure message, matching the structure expected by MCE implementations.\n"
}